# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository.
# On checkout, git will convert to the OS-native line ending (CRLF on Windows).
# On commit, git will normalize back to LF.
# This ensures CI (Linux) sees LF files and Prettier doesn't report CRLF diffs.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Exceptions for files that must remain binary or have specific encodings.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.lock binary
